## 7. Operational Risk

---

Risk — Model drift degrading output quality over time

Impact — Cohere model updates or shifts in enterprise data distribution can cause silent degradation in output accuracy — creating downstream errors in member service, document processing, or compliance workflows.

Mitigation — Implement ongoing performance monitoring with defined thresholds triggering review. Align to SR 11-7 ongoing monitoring requirements. Establish a model change management process that includes regression testing before production updates.

Severity — 🔴 High

Frameworks — SR 11-7, NIST AI RMF MANAGE

---

Risk — Integration failure between Cohere and legacy systems

Impact — API failures, schema mismatches, or latency spikes between Cohere and enterprise systems (CRM, claims platforms, knowledge bases) could disrupt member-facing services.

Mitigation — Design integration layer with circuit breakers and graceful degradation. Test integration points in staging before production deployment. Include Cohere API dependencies in incident response runbooks.

Severity — 🟡 Medium

Frameworks —*NIST CSF, ISO 27001

---

Risk — Shadow AI deployment outside governance framework

Impact — Business units could independently deploy Cohere APIs without AI governance review — creating untracked model risk, data exposure, and compliance gaps invisible to the enterprise risk function.

Mitigation — Publish an approved AI tools list and intake process. Enforce API key provisioning through the AI governance team. Conduct quarterly shadow AI audits across business units. Communicate consequences of non-sanctioned deployments.

Severity — 🟡 Medium

Frameworks — NIST AI RMF GOVERN, SR 11-7

---

## 8. Reputational Risk

---

Risk — Biased or discriminatory AI outputs affecting members

Impact — Cohere outputs used in member communications, service routing, or decisioning could reflect training data biases — resulting in disparate treatment findings, regulatory action, and media exposure.

Mitigation — Conduct bias evaluation before deployment of any member-facing use case. Test across protected class proxies aligned to ECOA and fair lending requirements. Document bias testing methodology and results in the model risk dossier.

Severity — 🔴 High

Frameworks - ECOA, CFPB, EU AI Act

---

Risk — Hallucinated outputs damaging member trust

Impact — Cohere generating factually incorrect information about policies, benefits, or account details — delivered to members or staff — erodes trust and creates potential liability.

Mitigation — Use RAG architecture with grounded retrieval to anchor responses in verified enterprise content. Implement confidence thresholds with fallback to human agents below threshold. Add visible AI disclosure to member-facing interactions.

Severity — 🟡 Medium

Frameworks — NIST AI RMF, CFPB

---

Risk — Negative public perception of AI adoption

Impact — Public or employee backlash against AI use in financial services could damage brand reputation, particularly if adoption outpaces transparent communication.

Mitigation —* Develop internal and external AI transparency communications. Publish AI use principles on the enterprise website. Engage employee communications teams before major AI deployments. Monitor media and social sentiment.

Severity — 🟢 Low

Frameworks — NIST AI RMF GOVERN

